{{champion:23}} {{champion:27}} {{champion:24}} 

Right idea wrong lane.
Toplane is where you can apply a lot of pressure. You have to trust your own play, but if you get the practice in you will ruin games. Bronze and Silver (even my Plat friend) just don't respond to splitpushes well. They will chase and lose mid or they will ignore and lose inhib. 

{{champion:83}} 
Is ok. Even when I beat him in lane in bronze, he would still get first inhib if I stop pushing top. 
{{champion:74}} 
Should be easy enough for a few bronze games.
